                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d393fn1">Sent by the White House Map Room, via military
                        channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-29">29 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Deliver to Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> from the
                    President. Your message transmitted as <gloss target="#t_White1">White</gloss>
                        55,<note n="2" xml:id="d393fn2">Telegram printed <hi rend="italic"
                        >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_616">p. 616</ref>.</note> I think it more
                    advisable to appoint <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName> as our
                        representative.<note n="3" xml:id="d393fn3">On November 2, 1943, <persName
                            corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName> at London had cabled <persName
                            corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> at Washington that he “would like
                        to have a chance to serve on the European Advisory Commission”. (<persName
                            corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers)</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
